c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-59_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-58_">01. How To Clean Precious Metals</h1><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-62_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">All of our jewelry is made with solid gold and platinum, preventing any tarnishing issues that may result in metals such as silver. Most naturally occuring discoloration can be easily solved by gently polishing your metal with a soft cloth. For chains, we recommend using a soft bristled toothbrush and a warm soap and water mixture to cautiously push the bristles through each link</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-72_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-71_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-66_">02. Diamonds Are Resilient</h1><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-68_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As the strongest and most resilient of all gemstones, diamonds can stand the test of time...which also means they’re a breeze to clean. They’re resistance to daily wear and tear allows them to withstand regular cleaning. We suggest soaking your diamond pieces in a soapy solution with warm water for a short period of time and gently clean with a very soft brush. To dry your jewelry, simply polish with a dry, lint free cloth and watch your diamonds sparkle like new.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-78_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-77_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-74_">03. Be Gentle With Gemstones</h1><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-76_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Gemstone durability is graded from zero to ten, according to the gem’s hardiness. While diamonds register at ten, with sapphires and rubies at nine, softer stones such as emeralds and tanzanites that score between six and eight require more specialist care and won’t survive abrasive cleaning detergents. Use a soft cloth only to avoid any unwanted scratches or inflicting damage to the integrity of your stone. Avoid all harsh chemicals and excessive heat sources as that can lead to cracking later down the road.&nbsp;<br></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-84_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-83_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-80_">04. Don't Forget Your Storage</h1><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-82_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">All jewelry is susceptible to damage and tarnishing when exposed to extreme heat or humid climates. Make sure to invest in a safe jewelry box to house all of your pieces. Look for containers that offer organization designed specifically for each item and type of jewelry; keep in mind that your pieces should not be touching or tangled together and to keep different metals separated from each other.&nbsp;<br></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-120_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-119_"><h1 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-116_">05. R&amp;R Service</h1><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-118_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Sometimes your JT piece just need a spa day. Whether that's just a deep cleaning or checking to make sure your stones are secure, our concierge team w